<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="157" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="157">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="157">
This species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. bistripustulata" pageId="0" pageNumber="157" rank="species" species="bistripustulata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="157">B. bistripustulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and other species of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1801" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Brachiacantha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Brachiacantha dentipes" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="157" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dentipes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="157">Brachiacantha dentipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. The principal difference is the male genitalia with a robust curved hook and male ventral cusps longer than wide. The cusps in the third ventrite are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. blaisdelli" pageId="0" pageNumber="157" rank="species" species="blaisdelli">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="157">B. blaisdelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Nunenmacher, but the male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName genus="B." lsidName="B. robustihamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="157" rank="species" species="robustihamata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="157">B. robustihamata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distinguished by the curved hook.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
